Today’s hearing was no sham.

@FinancialCmte Republicans are committed to understanding the threats facing our constituents and the factors contributing to the increase in financial fraud and scams.

We need a whole-of-society approach. https://t.co/bQ6aQqtdMS

Today, I made clear: community banks drive Main Street growth, but ideological rules and subjective examinations hold them back.

Under the Trump administration, we will focus on creating a regulatory environment where examinations are clear, consistent, and fair — so community banks can focus on lending, not second-guessing shifting standards. That starts at the CFPB.

@FinancialCmte Republicans are committed to making it easier — not harder — for community banks to serve small businesses and local economies.

As the first piece of legislation considered in this new Congress, House Republicans reaffirmed our commitment to securing the border, addressing illegal immigration, and keeping our communities safe.
 
This afternoon, I voted for the Laken Riley Act, an important bill that protects our communities by ensuring illegal immigrants who commit crimes like theft, burglary, and shoplifting—just as Laken Riley’s killer had—are detained and deported before they can commit violent acts against Americans.
 
@HouseGOP will continue to fight to protect our communities and put America First.
